# 📂 01 — PLanning

**Business function:** Background Art Production — 2D Animation Studio
**Trigger:** New episode script or revised script received from director or production coordinator
**Prompts in this section:** P01, P02

---

## Section Purpose

This section supports the initial planning stage of background production in a 2D animation studio. It focuses on transforming raw script content into structured, production-ready information and prioritising workload based on complexity and deadlines.

By automating script interpretation and task prioritisation, this section reduces manual planning effort, improves alignment across the team, and ensures that high-risk or complex scenes are identified early in the pipeline.

## Chain Diagram (if applicable)

```
Director sends episode script → [P01 RUNS — extracts all unique background locations] → Supervisor reviews and approves location list → [P02 RUNS — ranks locations by deadline and complexity] → Department lead approves ranked work order → Work order distributed to artists → 02-pre-production begins

